JD - 1 :

What You Will Be Doing
- Giving technical support and advice to sales
- Having good relationship with R & D engineers and managers
- Supporting customers in terms of technical advice, component selection, and troubleshooting
- Finding out new potential customers in India.
- Leading sales to right way and giving good advice and support for design IN &WIN
- Keeping database effective
- Providing application/component information to divisions in support of new product development.

What You Will Bring Along
- Bachelor’s degree in electronic and electrical engineering or equivalent qualification.
- Minimum 5 years pf relevant experience in Field Application Engineering or project design engineering field in hardware, circuit and electronics engineering/component industries.
- Strong understanding of electronic components, working experience with resistors/capacitors/inductors/diodes/ MOSFETs is preferred.
- Ability to provide technical advice and troubleshooting component-level issues.
- Knowledge of component selection and application in analog circuits such as Switching Power Supply, Buck/Boost converter, OBC, BMS, ADAS, DCDC, and Inverter. 
- Proven experience in technical sales support or application engineering roles is highly recommended.
- Experience identifying new business opportunities and potential customers.
- Knowledge of the Indian electronics market, including trends and key players is highly recommended.
- Willingness to travel extensively (over 50%) for customer meetings, technical support, and industry events.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

JD - 2 :

Key Responsibilities
- Provide pre-sales and post-sales technical support to customers for MPS products
- Work directly with customers’ engineering teams to understand system requirements and recommend suitable power solutions.
- Support design-in and design-win activities, including schematic reviews, component selection, and system optimization.
- Deliver product demonstrations, technical presentations, and training to customers and internal sales teams.
- Assist customers with board bring-up, debugging, troubleshooting hardware and system-level issues.
- Analyze customer issues and coordinate with R&D and product engineering teams to resolve complex technical problems.
- Develop and maintain application notes, technical documentation, and reference designs.
- Gather customer feedback and market insights to support product improvement and roadmap planning.
- Support customer evaluations, prototypes, and qualification processes.
- Travel to customer sites as required to provide on-site technical support.

Required Qualifications
- 8+ years of experience in FAE, hardware design, Power Architecture or applications engineering.
- Bachelor’s degree in electrical engineering, Electronics Engineering, or a related field.
- Strong understanding of Power semiconductor devices and electronic systems.
- Understanding of most common power supply architecture, DCDC converter/Controllers, AC-DC Topologies
- Experience with Analog, digital, power, or mixed-signal ICs
- Ability to read and analyze schematics, datasheets, and PCB layouts.
- Hands-on experience with lab equipment (oscilloscopes, logic analyzers, multimeters, power supplies).
- Strong problem-solving and debugging skills.
- Excellent communication and presentation skills.

Preferred Qualifications
- Experience in specific domains such as power management in Energy Meters, UPS/Inverters, Automotive electronics, and industrial
- Familiarity with power Architecture, firmware, or software tools.
- Knowledge of industry standards and compliance requirements (EMI /EMC)
- Customer-facing or technical Support experience. Work Environment
- Combination of office, laboratory, and customer-site work
- Moderate travel required
- Fast-paced, customer-focused environment

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

JD - 3 :

In your new role you will:
- Actively working towards achieving the Design Win Targets of the Automotive segment products in India.
- Technical support to direct OEMs/Tier-1s, distribution customers and design-houses to enable rapid adoption of Infineon products.
- Working dedicatedly on joint development projects with customers as and when needed.
- Working closely with Sales/Marketing, Distribution, Application Engineers in other regions to achieve the targets & collaborate.
- Performing technical analysis of circuits/boards to resolve issues or meet customers’ criteria or benchmarking against competitors’ products.
- Working on proof of concepts/demonstrators/reference solutions to support customers & build system knowledge.
- Capturing & feeding the regional requirements, product issues/fixes &improvement ideas to Headquarters through Regional Centre.
- Preparing the training material & conducting technical trainings, workshops and seminars in India.
- Preparing presentations, technical documents, application notes, SAE Papers, Patent Ideas, etc.
- Troubleshooting of FAR issues on application level and propose effective solutions.

You are best equipped for this task if you have:
- More than 5 years of application engineering or embedded(hardware/software) development experience, preferably in Automotive domain.
- Experience with different types of (Magnetic/Halleffect/Piezo/Capacitive/MEMS) Sensors, Secure Connectivity & power semiconductors &products.
- Exposure to different types of Motors, Motor Control techniques, software algorithms, sensing methodologies & other Electric vehicles applications such as DC-DC Converters, Battery Management Systems will be an added advantage.
- Hands-on with Microcontrollers, Peripherals, Tools & Ecosystem would be preferred.
- Should be able to work with Multimeter, Oscilloscope, Function Generator, Protocol Analyzers, etc. for testing & debugging.
- Other Special Skills / Attributes:
- Willing to travel within India on short notice
- Good presentation & communication skills
- Target Oriented and an excellent team player
- Quick learner and high technical orientation
- Ability to work under pressure and willing to travel frequently
- Analytical & problem solver

